Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: The Stand in the Schoolhouse Door of 1963
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yds18
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 17 Jun 1988
Cooke recalls the moment when the segregationist George Wallace, Governor of Alabama, attempted to prevent a black student enrolling at the University of Alabama in 1963.